      "content": "The \"living constitution\" approach is not \"illegitimate\" in the sense of being illegal, but it is fundamentally *unprincipled* when compared to originalism. It is a philosophical justification for judicial policymaking, allowing judges to substitute their contemporary social views for the settled meaning of the text. While it offers flexibility, that flexibility is precisely what makes it susceptible to political bias rather than legal restraint.",
      "source": "target",
